reviewText: Didn't keep the kids' interest through the whole time...not sure why not. I can't say I found it worth 4 bucks (let alone 8 to buy) for what boiled down to a double length episode. Given 1.99/episode, this should cost 5 bucks to buy at most.
summary: Meh...at least it was genuinely *christmas* and not some winter holiday...
Title: N/A

reviewText: If you are a Dora fan, this is a must.  My child loves Dora and I, as an adult, even rate this as one of the best Christmas movies.  The format is similar to any TV Dora episode, except more drawn out.  The story focuses on helping Swiper turn good for Christmas with the help of Dora.  My child is 3 years old and this movie really impressed upon him not to get on the naughty list like Swiper.
summary: If you love Dora, get this

reviewText: I bought this version of A Christmas Carol because I collect film versions of A Christmas Carol, and was disappointed to discover that it is not based on the Charles Dickens classic.It's more about Santa Claus' lists of who's naughty and nice.
